propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propComponent:
The component used for the root node.
Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propDense:
If `true`, compact vertical padding designed for keyboard and mouse input is used.
The prop defaults to the value inherited from the parent List component.
propDisableGutters: If `true`, the left and right padding is removed.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesGutters: Styles applied to the root element unless `disableGutters={true}`.
stylesSelected: Styles applied to the root element if `selected={true}`.
stylesDense: Styles applied to the root element if dense.
